    <title>Apple’s AirTags have dropped to one of their best prices to date  </title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="AirTagsA" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/peM01MwEOwA3u9H0I90aejn-VWs=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73695644/vpavic_4547_20210421_0074.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;Let’s face it, you’d be hard-pressed to find a better location tracker if you’re tapped into the Apple ecosystem.&lt;/em&gt; | Photo: Vjeran Pavic / The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="sRVvf4"&gt;Thanksgiving is just around the corner, meaning airports everywhere are about to get slammed. Thankfully, if you plan on flying out of town this holiday season, &lt;strong&gt;Apple’s AirTags&lt;/strong&gt; can help you speed through the baggage claim with some extra piece of mind. A four-pack normally goes for $99, but right now, you can buy them for just under $74 at &lt;a href="https://goto.walmart.com/c/482924/565706/9383?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmart.com%2Fip%2FApple-AirTag-4-Pack%2F5395277557&amp;amp;sharedid=theverge.com" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Walmart&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://howl.link/nd608lbftysay"&gt;Best Buy&lt;/a&gt; — a mere $1 shy of their best price to date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="KBviCy"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"All the news from Apple’s ‘week’ of Mac announcements","url":"https://www.theverge.com/24279307/apple-mac-m4-updates-news-announcements"},{"title":"Here’s where you can preorder the new MacBook Pro, iMac, and Mac Mini","url":"https://www.theverge.com/24279801/apple-macbook-pro-mac-mini-imac-m4-preorder-buy-price-release-date"},{"title":"Bose is taking up to 40 percent off headphones ahead of Black Friday","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/11/1/24285396/bose-quietcomfort-ultra-headphones-backbone-one-controller-deal-sale"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="e5iHem"&gt;If you own an iPhone, Apple’s AirTags are the &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23769840/best-bluetooth-trackers"&gt;best Bluetooth trackers you can buy&lt;/a&gt;. They offer impressively precise tracking thanks to Apple’s ultra wideband chip and their ability to tap into Apple’s vast Find My system, which lets them cover a broader range than Bluetooth alone. You can also &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/6/23751614/apple-airtag-find-my-sharing-ios-17-feature"&gt;share them with up to five people&lt;/a&gt; — assuming...&lt;/p&gt;
